Spring Quarter, 2023      Registration for term ends on Wednesday, March 15, 2023


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

Ac Eng 20 courses:
  ~ Students are required to take the Academic English
  ~     Placement Test prior to enrolling in AC ENG 20
  ~     courses.  Dates of the placement test can be
  ~     obtained by contacting the UCI Academic Testing
  ~     Center at (949) 824-6207, or testcenter@uci.edu,
  ~     or via their web site at
  ~     http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###

   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###

   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The Enrollment Exception     ###
   ###  form is available on Student Access.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 17, 2023. Restrictions are lifted at the discretion of the ###
   ###  department.                                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  How to enroll for next quarter:                                  ###
   ###  http://www.arts.uci.edu/student-affairs-next-quarter-enroll. For ###
   ###  additional questions, email artscounselor@uci.edu                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                     Art

        Enrolled students must attend the first day of instruction.
        Enrolled students who do not attend or are late for the first
        day of instruction, may be dropped from the course at the
        instructor's discretion. Students will be responsible for
        officially dropping the course.

        Course material fees are non-refundable, unless the class is
        dropped AND the student notifies the Department of Art
        administrative office by MONDAY OF WEEK 3.Fees will not be
        refunded beyond the Monday of Week 3; no exceptions. If a
        student drops the course beyond Week 3, the student will still
        be held accountable for paying the course material fee.

        Students who wish to waive the optional course material fee must
        inform the instructor with justification AND notify the Art
        administrative office by MONDAY OF WEEK 3. Fees will not be
        waived beyond the Monday of Week 3; no exceptions.

        Students are welcome to enroll in courses when the major
        restrictions are removed; see above for the date/time when major
        restrictions will be removed. If classes are full, students are
        encouraged to enroll in the Wait List, if available. Students on
        the Wait List are advised to attend the first day of class.

        Instructors will give "add" and "drop" codes through the second
        week of classes, based on availability.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The Enrollment Exception     ###
   ###  form is available on Student Access.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Biological   ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5PM with the exception of       ###
   ###  Upper-Division Labs, Bio Sci 100, and Bio Sci D170 that have a   ###
   ###  drop deadline of THURSDAY, MARCH 30th by 5pm. Drops can be made  ###
   ###  in WebReg.                                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ALL BIOLOGICAL SCIENCES COURSES ARE INITIALLY RESTRICTED TO      ###
   ###  MAJORS IN THE SCHOOL OF BIOLOGICAL SCIENCES UNTIL MARCH 20th AT  ###
   ###  NOON.                                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Biological     ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of week 2 at 5PM. Adds can be made in        ###
   ###  WebReg. Students are responsible for all materials from the      ###
   ###  start of the term. Failure to take any exams or quizzes, even    ###
   ###  those given before you have added the course, will result in a   ###
   ###  zero score for each quiz or exam.                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                             Biological Sciences

        SCHOOL/MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: All BIO SCI courses will initially be
        RESTRICTED to majors in the School of Biological Sciences ONLY. 
        Note that some courses may be additionally restricted to
        specific majors.  These major specific restrictions will lift
        (with the exception of major specific seminar courses) March
        13th by noon and at that point will be available to all majors
        within the School of Biological Sciences. For detailed
        information about course enrollment and restrictions go to:
        http://undergraduate.bio.uci.edu/student-affairs/enrollment-updates/.

        For students NOT in the School of Biological Sciences, the
        school major restriction will lift MARCH 20th by noon.

        REPEAT RESTRICTIONS: Students who wish to enroll to repeat a
        core, upper-division elective, or lab course will be restricted
        from enrolling until noon on MARCH 20th.

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may become eligible to
        enroll in a particular UCI Bio Sci course by completing the "Bio
        Course Prerequisite Clearance Form" on the Bio Sci Student
        Affairs the form on the Bio Sci Student Affairs website:
        http://undergraduate.bio.uci.edu/student-affairs/forms/ a
        minimum of two days before their window opens. Once students
        have had their prerequisites cleared they will remain eligible
        for one quarter, with the exception of Bio 199 (clearance
        remains for the academic year).

        LAB COURSES:

        BIO LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY!!!!

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS OF ANY BIO SCI UPPER-DIVISON LABS, Bio
        Sci 100, and Bio Sci D170 AFTER THURSDAY, MARCH 30th. This
        deadline is earlier than the School of Biological Sciences Week
        2 deadline.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

    The column headings above are defined at:
	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/help/WebSoc-Columns.shtml
    Course textbooks link:
	    http://uci.bncollege.com
    Building Abbreviations:
	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/uci/rooms
    Campus map:
	    http://www.uci.edu/campusmap

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    K: Graduate only

                                  Chemistry

        Please visit the Chemistry Policy website at
        http://www.chem.uci.edu/schedulepolicy for additional
        information on Chemistry undergraduate course enrollment
        procedures and frequently asked questions. This includes
        information on repeat and major restrictions, important
        laboratory information, and how to clear your prerequisites. If
        you still have questions after reviewing the Chemistry Policy
        website, please email chemistry@uci.edu.

        Classes are subject to change. Check the Schedule of Classes for
        possible changes before classes begin.

        Prerequisites and corequisites are actively checked. Click the
        "Prerequisite" or "Corequisite" link by each course for
        up-to-date requirements.

        There will be no changes to Chemistry labs after week 1. Please
        note: This deadline is earlier than the School of Physical
        Sciences week 2 deadline. Attendance for week 1 is mandatory.
        Lab Fees are non-refundable. Please see the Chemistry Policy
        website at http://www.chem.uci.edu/schedulepolicy for details. 

        If you don't meet the prerequisites for the course, you will be
        dropped from the course by the Chemistry Department.

        Major restrictions will be lifted on Monday, March 20, by
        12:00pm. The repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday, April
        3, by 12:00pm.

Chem course numbers 200 - 399:
  ~ Graduate Students: Choose the letter grade option for
  ~     the core graduate courses. If you choose to take
  ~     an additional course for the S/U option, contact
  ~     the professor of the course.
  ~ Chem 299 enrollment requires permission from the
  ~     instructor.
  ~ Undergraduate students who want to enroll in graduate
  ~     level courses: Contact the faculty member to
  ~     obtain permission before your enrollment window
  ~     opens. Students will have access to the course on
  ~     WebReg once the instructor sends the notification
  ~     of approval to the Chemistry Undergraduate Office
  ~     (chemistry@uci.edu).
  ~ Unauthorized students will be dropped from the
  ~     course.

   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

        first time in Spring 2023 must complete a placement assessment

        &lt;rhsieh@uci.edu&gt;.

        Students registered in any section of Chinese 1C/1MC, 2C, or 3C
        MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meetings. Any student who
        does not meet this condition will be required to drop the class.

   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        drop the course.

        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                              Computer Science

         RESTRICTIONS: COMPSCI courses will initially be restricted to
        majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors or level(s) of standing. For restriction details
        and timeline:
        http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php

        WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in
        communication with that course's instructor to arrange for
        access to course materials and submission of any assignments
        while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing
        coursework DOES NOT guarantee a seat in the course.

        DISCUSSION &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs,
        ICS 364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs
        are required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

        B or X Restricted Courses: Courses with a B or X restriction
        require an authorization code from the instructor to enroll.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at https://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until Tuesday, March 14th at noon.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please note: The majority of classes in the School of Social     ###
   ###  Ecology will be restricted to specific schools or majors until   ###
   ###  Tuesday, March 14th by noon. whether or not an L or N            ###
   ###  restriction is listed in the Restrictions column on the Schedule ###
   ###  of Classes. Please visit the General Catalogue to see which      ###

   ###  time.                                                            ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The Enrollment Exception     ###
   ###  form is available on Student Access.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 17, 2023. Restrictions are lifted at the discretion of the ###
   ###  department.                                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  How to enroll for next quarter:                                  ###
   ###  http://www.arts.uci.edu/student-affairs-next-quarter-enroll. For ###
   ###  additional questions, email artscounselor@uci.edu                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The Enrollment Exception     ###
   ###  form is available on Student Access.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 17, 2023. Restrictions are lifted at the discretion of the ###
   ###  department.                                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  How to enroll for next quarter:                                  ###
   ###  http://www.arts.uci.edu/student-affairs-next-quarter-enroll. For ###
   ###  additional questions, email artscounselor@uci.edu                ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Economics

        Departmental drop/add policy

        Drops:

        Students may drop Economics courses only through the second week
        of the quarter. After the second week, permission to drop will
        NOT be granted by the instructor.

        Adds:

        The Department of Economics' policy on adds remains unchanged,
        and follows that of the School of Social Sciences. For more
        information please visit the website:
        http://www.economics.uci.edu/index.php?p=37
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Program in Public      ###
   ###  Health is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the Program in Public Health is Week    ###
   ###  10. Change of grade options or variable units beginning weeks    ###
   ###  3-6 must be made through Student Access/Enrollment Exceptions.   ###
   ###  Major requirements for the Program in Public Health must be      ###
   ###  taken for a letter grade. Chair's signature can be obtained in   ###
   ###  the Program in Public Health Student Affairs Office, located in  ###
   ###  AIRB 2010.                                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Program in Public Health ###
   ###  is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.   ###
   ###  Students are responsible for all materials from the start of the ###
   ###  term. Failure to take any exams or quizzes, even those given     ###
   ###  before you have added the course, will result in a zero score    ###
   ###  for each quiz or exam.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDITIONAL UNITS: If you wish to enroll in more than 18 units,   ###
   ###  please be aware, the Student Affairs Office will not do this     ###
   ###  until the University restriction has been lifted, which will be  ###
   ###  on March 18th at noon. After that date, students will be able to ###
   ###  enroll in up to 20 units. For more than 20 units, please contact ###
   ###  phuao@uci.edu on or after March 18th.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###

   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###

   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###

                                   English

        Students registered in any course offered by the Department of
        English are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND CLASS
        MEETINGS of the course or they may be required to drop the
        course.

        Please be advised that some English courses will have a "B" or
        "X" restriction starting on the first day of instruction.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
