   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     Program in Public Health                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Program in Public      ###
   ###  Health is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the Program in Public Health is Week    ###
   ###  10. Change of grade options or variable units beginning weeks    ###
   ###  3-6 must be made through Student Access/Enrollment Exceptions.   ###
   ###  Major requirements for the Program in Public Health must be      ###
   ###  taken for a letter grade. Chair's signature can be obtained in   ###
   ###  the Program in Public Health Student Affairs Office, located in  ###
   ###  AIRB 2010.                                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Program in Public Health ###
   ###  is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.   ###
   ###  Students are responsible for all materials from the start of the ###
   ###  term. Failure to take any exams or quizzes, even those given     ###
   ###  before you have added the course, will result in a zero score    ###
   ###  for each quiz or exam.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDITIONAL UNITS: If you wish to enroll in more than 18 units,   ###
   ###  please be aware, the Student Affairs Office will not do this     ###
   ###  until the University restriction has been lifted, which will be  ###
   ###  on March 18th at noon. After that date, students will be able to ###
   ###  enroll in up to 20 units. For more than 20 units, please contact ###
   ###  phuao@uci.edu on or after March 18th.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                Epidemiology

        ADD/DROP: The policy of the Department of Epidemiology is that
        all 199 Adds and Drops must be finalized with the University
        Registrar prior to the end of the second week of instruction.
        Before this deadline, adds and drops can be accomplished
        electronically through the WebReg.

        EPIDEM course numbers were previously listed under ENVIRON in
        the School of Social Ecology.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

                                   Finance

        Master of Finance classes are restricted to Master of Finance
        students only. Non-Master of Finance graduate students
        interested in adding a Master of Finance course may contact
        their Program Manager or the Master of Finance Program Office by
        email at sfazli@uci.edu

        RESTRICTIONS: ALL FIN Core classes and some elective courses
        will reamin major restricted.

        PREREQUISITES: Vary by class. Please check with your Program
        Manager or with the Master of Finance Program Office by email at
        sfazli@uci.edu.

       _________________________________________________________________

                           Film and Media Studies

        Film viewing takes place in the studio sections. Attendance is
        mandatory. Enrollment in lecture and studio, or lecture and
        studio and discussion, where offered, is required for all Film &amp;
        Media Studies courses.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

        There is a mandatory non-refundable course material fee of
        $20.00 for all Film &amp; Media Studies courses, including
        cross-listed and concurrently scheduled courses. Upon
        enrollment, course fees are posted automatically to a student's
        ZOT Account. Students dropping before before the second week
        drop deadline (April 14th, 2023) may request a course fee
        cancellation or refund in writing by contacting the Film &amp; Media
        Studies Lab Fee Administrator, Sylvia Meza-Tallada at
        smezatal@uci.edu. No cancellation or refund will be made for an
        unpaid Course Fee that goes to a collection agency.

        Due to the volume of majors and incoming new students,
        enrollment on all of Film and Media courses will be restricted
        to majors only until Tuesday, March 7th, by noon.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   French

        TO ENROLL IN A FRENCH LANGUAGE CLASS: French placement testing
        is recommended, but not required for students who have
        successfully completed French classes in high school. Contact
        the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949)
        824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) French exam is eligible to enroll directly into French 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement French exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        French100A; however, full credit will be awarded for French 2C
        if the student wants to take French 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        French, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        French Language Program Director.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   German

        TO ENROLL IN A GERMAN LANGUAGE CLASS: For all German courses
        beyond 1A, placement testing is recommended for students who
        have had previous experience with or instruction in the
        language. Contact the UCI Humantities Studio at (949) 824-6344
        for placement test dates and details on registering for a
        placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) German exam is eligible to enroll directly into German 2A.
        A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement German exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        uppder-division German.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        German, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        For placement-related questions contact Language Program
        Director Mohammad Rafi (mrafi@uci.edu).

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Human 1 courses:
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE (course codes 27600-28130):
  ~ For more information about the Humanities Core course
  ~     sequence, visit http://core.humanities.uci.edu.
  ~ To ensure proper enrollment in both the Lecture and
  ~     Seminar, students must enroll in the Lecture
  ~     (LEC) first, and the Writing (WRT) second.
  ~ Students registered in any section of Humanities Core
  ~     are expected to attend both the FIRST and SECOND
  ~     class meetings of the course or they may be
  ~     required to drop the course.
  ~ HUMANITIES CORE ADD/DROP POLICY: ADDS must be
  ~     effected PRIOR to the END of the FIRST WEEK OF
  ~     CLASSES. DROPS must be effected PRIOR to the END
  ~     of the SECOND WEEK OF CLASSES.
  ~ After the second week, any exception to the two week
  ~     ADD/DROP deadline must be requested as an
  ~     Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess
  ~     system and requires approval of the Undergraduate
  ~     Dean.
  ~ All authorization codes for Humanities Core sections
  ~     are obtained from Humanities Core staff
  ~     (humcore@uci.edu) in the Humanities Core office
  ~     (HIB 185). Authorization codes will NOT be
  ~     provided by instructors in the individual course
  ~     sections.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

    A: Prerequisite required

    N: School major only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                      Information and Computer Science

        RESTRICTIONS: Most I&amp;C SCI courses will be initially RESTRICTED
        to majors in Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors or level(s) of standing. For restriction details
        and timeline:
        http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php

        WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in
        communication with that course's instructor to arrange for
        access to course materials and submission of any assignments
        while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing
        coursework DOES NOT guarantee a seat in the course.

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs,
        ICS 364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs
        are required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

        B or X Restricted Course: Courses with a B or X restriction
        require an authorization code from the instructor to enroll.

	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/help/WebSoc-Columns.shtml

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only
    X: Separate authorization codes required to add, drop, or change enrollment

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                 Informatics

         RESTRICTIONS: Most IN4MATX courses will be initially restricted
        to majors in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors or level(s) of standing. For restriction details
        and timeline:
        http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php

        WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in
        communication with that course's instructor to arrange for
        access to course materials and submission of any assignments
        while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing
        coursework DOES NOT guarantee a seat in that course.

        DISCUSSIONS &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        Some lab sections are scheduled in laptop instructional labs ICS
        364A, ICS2 162, or ICS2 170. Students enrolled in these labs are
        required to bring a personal laptop to class meetings.

         B or X Restricted Courses: Courses with a B or X restriction
        require an authorization code from the instructor to enroll.

    Values in the "Enr" column like "45/70" show "section / joint" enrollment
	totals for cross-listed courses.
    WL column entries like "off(3)" indicate the department turned off the course waitlist;
	this can prevent new students from adding the course if it is almost full.
	Students on the waitlist must be removed from the waitlist via WebReg during
	enrollment periods to allow maximum enrollment into the course.
    The column headings above are defined at:
	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/help/WebSoc-Columns.shtml

	    http://uci.bncollege.com

	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/uci/rooms
    Campus map:
	    http://www.uci.edu/campusmap

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    I: Seniors only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                            International Studies

        Department of Global and International Studies:
        http://www.globalstudies.uci.edu/index.php

        All International Studies course listings can be found at:
        http://www.globalstudies.uci.edu/undergrad/courses.php

        Enrollment in lecture and discussion (where offered), is
        required unless otherwise indicated. Choose discussion directly
        below lecture.

        If an Undergraduate or Graduate course has a "B" or "X"
        restriction, please contact the course instructor directly for
        the authorization codes.

        Course offerings/times/days/locations are subject to change
        without notice. Check WebSOC for latest updates.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Italian

        TO ENROLL IN A ITALIAN LANGUAGE CLASS: Italian placement testing
        is recommended, but not required for students who have
        successfully completed Italian classes in high school. Contact
        the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, (949)
        824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a placement test.

        A student who received a score of "3" on the Advanced Placement
        (AP) Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into Italian
        2A. A student who received a score of "4" or "5" on the Advanced
        Placement Italian exam is eligible to enroll directly into
        Italian 100A; however, full credit will be awarded for Italian
        2C if the student wants to take Italian 2C first for review.

        Students with credit for previous college-level courses in
        Italian, contact your home academic counseling office to
        determine the appropriate course to enroll in at UCI.

        Any placement exceptions must have the written approval of the
        Italian Language Program Director.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, contact the Instructor
        to obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of
        the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

                                  Japanese

        Students registered in any section of Japanese 1C, 2C, or 3C
        MUST ATTEND THE FIRST and SECOND class meetings. Any student who
        does not meet this condition will be required to drop the class.

        Students wanting to enroll in a Japanese 1C, 2C, or 3C class for
        the first time at UCI in spring 2023 are required to take the
        Japanese placement test on Wednesday, February 8, 2023. An oral
        interview is also required to finalize your placement. The
        interview is scheduled at 11:45am-12:45pm on Monday, February
        13, 2023 in HIB 448. It is on a first come first served basis
        and an appointment is not necessary.

        For additional information, please contact Hidemi Riggs,
        Japanese Language Academic Coordinator at &lt;hriggs@uci.edu&gt;.

        Contact the UCI Academic Testing Center through their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/, by phone at (949) 824-6207,
        or by email at testcenter@uci.edu for details about test
        registration.

        If a class has a "B" or "X" restriction, email hriggs@uci.edu to
        obtain a code to add, drop, or change the grading option of the
        class.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Korean

        TO ENROLL IN A KOREAN LANGUAGE CLASS:

        Students who have prior experience with the Korean language and
        intend to enroll in a Korean language class for the first time
        in Spring 2023, MUST take a placement test. Testing is offered
        online. Students may register for this exam through the UCI
        Academic Testing Center website,
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu. For additional information,
        email the UCI Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu or call
        949-824-6207.

        After the test, appear for a Faculty Oral Interview to get your
        placement and obtain authorization to register for Korean class.
        Interview is offered on February 15-16, 2023, 1pm-2pm, in HIB
        375. The oral interview will be conducted on a
        first-come-first-served basis. Be sure to bring your language
        background survey form and your student ID card with you at the
        time of the interview. For inquiries about the Faculty Oral
        Interview, contact Hyunyoung Hyun, Korean Language Program
        Coordinator at hhyun@uci.edu

        Students registered in any section of Korean 1C, 2C, or 3C MUST
        attend the first and second class meeting of the course. Any
        student who does not meet this condition will be required to
        drop the class.
       _________________________________________________________________

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                 Mathematics

        Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information##3
        for the Department's Add/Drop and Waitlist Policy. Many sections
        will fill to capacity, so plan schedules carefully.

        Being on the electronic waitlist does NOT guarantee you a seat
        in the course.

        All upper division Math courses will be restricted to Math
        majors until 12:00pm on Friday, March 18th.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to
        http://math.uci.edu/undergrad-courses/course-registration-and-placement-information#Top
        for additional information on Mathematics undergraduate course
        enrollment procedures. Graduate students have last priority in
        enrollment in undergraduate courses.

        All upper division Math courses will be restricted to Math
        majors until 12:00pm on Monday, March 20th.

        MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Major Restrictions will be lifted on Monday,
        March 20th by 12:00 pm. Math majors will have first priority to
        enroll in all upper division undergraduate courses until the
        restriction is lifted.

        REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,
        please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,
        March 20th, by 12:00pm.

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###

                                 Management

        RESTRICTIONS: Due to the high volume of majors, enrollment in
        most Paul Merage School of Business undergraduate courses will
        be restricted to majors only until Thursday, March 16th at noon.
        Some courses will remain major restricted.

        PREREQUISITES: If you received AP credit or transferred courses
        that are considered a prerequisite, please fill out the form at
        the following link: http://bit.ly/2IwvEoO

        EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-units initially.
        The restriction will lift to 20-units on March 20th at noon. If
        you would like to enroll in more than 20-units, you can submit a
        form requesting excess units after this date at the following
        link: http://bit.ly/36AahLB

        MGMT 190s: Course descriptions and prerequisites for the Spring
        2022 Mgmt 190s can be found at the following link:
        http://bit.ly/3HnrQkw

    A: Prerequisite required
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only
    X: Separate authorization codes required to add, drop, or change enrollment
</pre></body></html><html><head><meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"></head><body><pre style="word-wrap: break-word; white-space: pre-wrap;">			UC Irvine Office of the Registrar

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                Henry Samueli School of Engineering                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Important Information                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL AND MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: School and major restrictions can ###
   ###  be found in the 2022-2023 UCI General Catalogue under each       ###
   ###  course description. The status of major restrictions will be     ###
   ###  updated throughout the enrollment period, and announcements will ###
   ###  be posted on the Engineering Teaching Plan -                     ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###   The Henry Samueli School of Engineering reserves the right to   ###
   ###  maintain major restrictions on impacted courses.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES: All undergraduate Engineering courses strictly    ###
   ###  enforce published prerequisites. Courses with co-requisites may  ###
   ###  require you to enroll in the co-requisite requirement before     ###
   ###  enrolling in the course. (Example: enrolling in EECS 170A and    ###
   ###  EECS 170LA. A student may need to enroll in EECS 170LA prior to  ###
   ###  enrolling in EECS 170A). If you are unable to enroll and you     ###
   ###  completed any prerequisites at another college or university,    ###
   ###  you will need to petition for course authorization. Please fill  ###
   ###  out the "Course Authorization" form                              ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms/course-authorization/),  ###
   ###  and click submit. The student will receive a response within 3-5 ###
   ###  business days from an Academic Counselor.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Select a form from the Engineering Website:                      ###
   ###  http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/forms. We encourage students to ###
   ###  read the directions and description of each form in its entirety ###
   ###  to ensure that you're completing the right form. If you have any ###
   ###  questions, please contact the Engineering Student Affairs Office ###
   ###  (http://undergraduate.eng.uci.edu/contact/contact-information/)  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEFICIENT GRADE: Students earning a deficient grade in a         ###
   ###  prerequisite course after enrolling will be dropped during the   ###
   ###  first week of class. Students should address any prior grade     ###
   ###  issues (NR, I, etc.) before the end of Week 1.                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FOR ENROLLMENT ASSISTANCE:                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you encounter an enrollment problem please email              ###
   ###  casa@eng.uci.edu or check for course announcements on the        ###
   ###  Engineering Teaching Plan -                                      ###
   ###  http://www.bit.ly/22-23UCIEngineeringTeachingPlan.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                 Claire Trevor School of the Arts                  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Claire Trevor School   ###
   ###  of the Arts is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Claire Trevor School of  ###
   ###  the Arts is the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  After these dates, requests to Add/Drop are considered through   ###
   ###  petition based on extenuating circumstances, requiring the       ###
   ###  approval of the Dean of the school offering the course as well   ###
   ###  as the Dean of the student's major. The Enrollment Exception     ###
   ###  form is available on Student Access.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please contact the faculty member directly for courses listed    ###
   ###  with a "B" (Authorization Code) restriction.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Major restrictions for some courses will be removed at noon on   ###
   ###  March 17, 2023. Restrictions are lifted at the discretion of the ###
   ###  department.                                                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  How to enroll for next quarter:                                  ###
   ###  http://www.arts.uci.edu/student-affairs-next-quarter-enroll. For ###
   ###  additional questions, email artscounselor@uci.edu                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                    Music

        Students who register in courses in private instrumental and
        vocal lessons (Music 65, 66, 67, 68, 69, 70, 165, 166, 167, 168,
        169, and 170) are assessed a course materials and service fee of
        $500. This fee is refundable if the course is dropped by the end
        of the second week of classes with the following conditions: (1)
        if no lesson has been given, the fee is refundable in full; (2)
        if one lesson has been given, the fee is refundable at the
        pro-rated amount of $444; (3) if two lessons have been given,
        the fee is refundable at the pro-rated amount of $400. Requests
        for a fee reversal should be directed to the Music Department
        office. No fee reversal will be made for courses dropped after
        the end of the second week of classes.
       _________________________________________________________________

Spring Quarter, 2023      Registration for term ends on Wednesday, March 15, 2023


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        more information.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

       _________________________________________________________________

                           Pharmaceutical Sciences

        PREREQUISITES: Students who have completed the equivalent of the
        prerequisites at another institution may verify eligibility to
        enroll in a particular UCI PharmSci course by emailing the
        Academic Counselors at pharmsci@uci.edu a minimum of three days
        before their registration window opens.

        REMINDERS: Courses must be taken for a grade to fulfill major
        requirements, unless the course is only offered on a P/NP basis.
        For PharmSci majors, BioSci 100 is the only exception and can be
        taken P/NP.

        Enrollment in discussion or lab may be required in addition to
        lecture. Choose from discussion or lab sections listed directly
        below the lecture.

        REPEATS: Students who wish to enroll to repeat a course they
        received a C- or lower in will be restricted from enrolling
        until noon on March 17th, 2023. MAJOR RESTRICTION: Students who
        are in majors other than PharmSci will not be able to enroll in
        major restricted classes (indicated with an "L") until March
        17th, 2023.

        MINIMUM GRADE POLICY

        Students must earn a grade of "C-" or above to advance to the
        next PharmSci core course, prerequisite course, and/or major
        requirement.For example, you must earn a "C-" or better grade in
        PharmSci 170A to move to Pharm Sci 170B. Please check the
        Pharmaceutical Sciences website for specific course requirement
        policies: http://pharmsci.uci.edu/undergraduate-students/.

        LAB COURSES:

        PHARM SCI LAB ENROLLMENT POLICY

        THERE WILL BE NO DROPS ALLOWED OF ANY PHARMSCI UPPER-DIVISION
        LABS AFTER MARCH 27th (DAY BEFORE CLASSES BEGIN). This deadline
        is earlier than the College of Health Sciences week 2 deadline.

        Lab fees of $75 are non-refundable. Payment due no later than
        Friday of Week 3.
