       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Physics

        Please refer to the WebSOC frequently for updates concerning
        course changes, including adds, cancellations, and day/time/room
        adjustments. Please also visit
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/ugrad/affairs for answers to
        frequently asked questions.

        ADDS/DROPS FOR PHYSICS COURSES 1 THROUGH 61:

        DROP LECTURE, DISCUSSION &amp; LAB: The deadline to drop any Physics
        course is Friday, April 7, 2023 (the end of Week 2). Drops must
        be made using WebReg. Students wishing to drop a course after
        that date must submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess
        and obtain the required approval of the Dean of student's major.
        Note that approval is NOT guaranteed and is usually only granted
        in extreme emergencies.

        ADD LAB: The deadline to add a Physics Lab is Friday, April 7,
        2023 (the end of Week 2). Adds must be made using WebReg.

        ADD LECTURE AND DISCUSSION: The deadline to add a Physics
        Lecture and Discussion is Friday, April 7, 2023 (the end of week
        2). Adds must be made using WebReg. NO ADDS WILL BE ALLOWED
        AFTER THIS DATE.

        Students who wish to make a grade option change before Friday,
        April 7, 2023 (the end of Week 2) should do so via WebReg.
        Students wishing to make a grade option change after that date
        must submit an Enrollment Exception via StudentAccess. Required
        approval is by the Dean of the student's major; approval is NOT
        guaranteed. Send enrollment questions to physics.enroll@uci.edu.

        STUDENTS WHO FAIL TO FILE AN OFFICIAL DROP WILL RECEIVE A GRADE
        OF "NR" IN THE COURSE. AN "NR" TURNS TO AN "F" OR "NP" AFTER ONE
        QUARTER OF ATTENDANCE.

        DISCUSSION SECTIONS:

        1. The Physics Tutoring Center is available to students in
        Physics 3, 7, 51, and 61. Please check
        http://www.physics.uci.edu/tutoring-schedule for scheduling.

        2. Enrollment in lecture and discussion is required. Most
        sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        discussion section.

        3. Attendance in your assigned discussion section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. No quizzes or exams will be graded for
        students who do not attend their assigned section.

        LABORATORY SECTIONS:

        1. Most sections fill to capacity so students should plan their
        schedules carefully and enroll as early as possible using
        WebReg. See above for information on how to add/drop a
        laboratory section.

        2. Attendance in your assigned laboratory section is MANDATORY
        throughout the quarter. Students will be allowed to participate
        in their assigned sections only.

        3. Lab manuals for Physics 3LB-LC, 7LD and 52A-B-C are available
        at the UCI Bookstore. Courses 3LB-LC and 52A-B-C also require
        the use of 5 blue books (grid) which must be purchased prior to
        WEEK ONE at the UCI Bookstore.

        4. LAB FEES: Students of Physics 3LB-LC, 7LC-LD, 52A-B-C, 121W
        and 206 will be charged a $25 lab fee. The charges for these
        classes will be added to your ZOT Bill Week 3 of the quarter.
        These charges will be posted Week 3 if you add a Physics lab
        after week one. The last day to add a lab is Friday, April 7,
        2023 (the end of Week 2).
       _________________________________________________________________

      ~    will be activated through Friday of second week. Placement on the
      ~    waitlist does not guarantee enrollment in the class. Students still
      ~    on the waitlist after the end of week 2 will not be added via the

      ~    system, you must add an open section using WebReg by the end of Week
      ~    2.

      ~    information regarding the waitlist system.

      ~    provided (1) their overall GPA is 3.0 or better, (2) their GPA in
      ~    Physics courses is 3.5 or better, (3) they have the approval of the

    A: Prerequisite required

    C: Fee required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    I: Seniors only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    M: Non-major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        the authorization codes.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at https://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until Tuesday, March 14th at noon.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please note: The majority of classes in the School of Social     ###
   ###  Ecology will be restricted to specific schools or majors until   ###
   ###  Tuesday, March 14th by noon. whether or not an L or N            ###
   ###  restriction is listed in the Restrictions column on the Schedule ###
   ###  of Classes. Please visit the General Catalogue to see which      ###
   ###  majors are eligible to add our lower division courses at this    ###
   ###  time.                                                            ###

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    G: Lower-division only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    M: Non-major only
    N: School major only
    S: Satisfactory/unsatisfactory only

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        an authorization code.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     Program in Public Health                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the Program in Public      ###
   ###  Health is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in   ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the Program in Public Health is Week    ###
   ###  10. Change of grade options or variable units beginning weeks    ###
   ###  3-6 must be made through Student Access/Enrollment Exceptions.   ###
   ###  Major requirements for the Program in Public Health must be      ###
   ###  taken for a letter grade. Chair's signature can be obtained in   ###
   ###  the Program in Public Health Student Affairs Office, located in  ###
   ###  AIRB 2010.                                                       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the Program in Public Health ###
   ###  is the Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.   ###
   ###  Students are responsible for all materials from the start of the ###
   ###  term. Failure to take any exams or quizzes, even those given     ###
   ###  before you have added the course, will result in a zero score    ###
   ###  for each quiz or exam.                                           ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDITIONAL UNITS: If you wish to enroll in more than 18 units,   ###
   ###  please be aware, the Student Affairs Office will not do this     ###
   ###  until the University restriction has been lifted, which will be  ###
   ###  on March 18th at noon. After that date, students will be able to ###
   ###  enroll in up to 20 units. For more than 20 units, please contact ###
   ###  phuao@uci.edu on or after March 18th.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                Public Health

        Public Health course offerings/times/days/locations are subject
        to change without notice. Check WEBSOC for latest updates.

        IMPORTANT: Refer to the Public Health Student Affairs Office or
        the Public Health website at: http://publichealth.uci.edu/ for
        additional information on Public Health course enrollment
        procedures and frequently asked questions, policies, and contact
        information.

        PREREQUISITES: Prerequisites may be cleared ahead of your
        registration date. Please e-mail Public Health Undergraduate
        Student Affairs at: phuao@uci.edu a minimum of one week before
        your registration window opens.

        REMINDERS: Courses must be taken for a letter grade to fulfill
        major requirements. Enrollment in discussion or lab may be
        required in addition to lecture. Choose from discussion or lab
        sections listed directly below the lecture.

        PRACTICUM: Undergraduate students must begin preparing for
        Practicum one to two quarters in advance. For information on
        procedures and deadlines, please visit:
        http://publichealth.uci.edu/ph/_app_undergraduate_practicum/procedures_deadlines.
        Please contact phpracticum@uci.edu with any questions regarding
        Practicum course enrollment.

        MAJOR RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in
        some Public Health courses will be restricted to Public Health
        majors only. Major restrictions will be lifted on March 20, 2023
        at noon.

        AUTHORIZATION CODES: Contact instructor or phuao@uci.edu, unless
        otherwise noted.

        WAITLIST: Placement on the waitlist does not guarantee
        enrollment in the class.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###

   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###

    Values in the "Enr" column like "73/73" show "section / joint" enrollment
	totals for cross-listed courses.
    WL column entries like "off(3)" indicate the department turned off the course waitlist;
	this can prevent new students from adding the course if it is almost full.
	Students on the waitlist must be removed from the waitlist via WebReg during
	enrollment periods to allow maximum enrollment into the course.

	    https://www.reg.uci.edu/help/WebSoc-Columns.shtml

Restriction Codes from the 'Rst' column above:
    A: Prerequisite required
    B: Authorization required
    D: Pass/not pass option only
    J: Upper-division only
    K: Graduate only
    L: Major only
    N: School major only

   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at https://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until Tuesday, March 14th at noon.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please note: The majority of classes in the School of Social     ###
   ###  Ecology will be restricted to specific schools or majors until   ###
   ###  Tuesday, March 14th by noon. whether or not an L or N            ###
   ###  restriction is listed in the Restrictions column on the Schedule ###
   ###  of Classes. Please visit the General Catalogue to see which      ###
   ###  majors are eligible to add our lower division courses at this    ###
   ###  time.                                                            ###

SocEcol  195       FIELD STUDY
      ~ Social Ecology 195 enrollment requires that students have formally
      ~    accepted a placement offer from a field study site and submitted a
      ~    course enrollment form by the appropriate deadline. For more
      ~    information about the process and deadlines apply to Field Study go
      ~    to http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures
      ~ SocEcol 195 is P/NP. Field Study is a variable unit course. Enroll via
      ~    WebReg entering the appropriate number of units in the unit box (1
      ~    unit/20 hours of field work).
      ~ The Field Study areas listed below reflect faculty departmental
      ~    affiliations and provide students with a general guideline with
      ~    which to select a Field Study course section.  It is recommended
      ~    (but NOT required) that students match their field placement site
      ~    with a course section in the appropriate area.
      ~ C sections are CLS Faculty
      ~ P sections are PSCI Faculty
      ~ U sections are UPPP Faculty
      ~ For more information on the difference between 195 and 195W go to:
      ~    http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/195-vs-195w
    CCode Typ Sec Unt  Instructor         Time              Place     Final                      Max     Enr      WL Req Nor Rstr Status

SocEcol  195W      FS WRITING SEMINAR
      ~ FS Writing Seminar Social Ecology 195W enrollment requires that
      ~    students have formally accepted a placement offer from a field study
      ~    site and submitted a course enrollment form by the appropriate
      ~    deadline. For more information about the process and deadlines to
      ~    apply to Field Study go to
      ~    http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-procedures
      ~ All students who meet the course enrollment prerequisites will be
      ~    guaranteed a spot in ScoEcol 195, Traditional Field Study.
      ~    Enrollment in SocEcol is NOT guaranteed as demand exceeds seats
      ~    available. Students will be able to enroll during their enrollment
      ~    window once 195W is full, students will need to enroll in 195. There
      ~    are other classes that can fulfill upper division writing.
      ~ SocEcol 195W must be taken for a letter grade. Field Study Writing
      ~    Seminar is a variable unit course. Enroll via WebReg entering the
      ~    appropriate number of units needed (1 unit/20 hours of field work).
      ~ The Field Study Areas listed below reflect faculty departmental
      ~    affiliations and provide students with a general guideline with
      ~    which to select a Field Study course section. It is recommended (but
      ~    NOT required) that students match their field placement site with a
      ~    course section in the appropriate area.
      ~ C sections are for CLS Faculty.
      ~ P sections are for PSCI Faculty.
      ~ U sections are for UPPP Faculty.
      ~ For more information on the difference between 195 and 195W go to:
      ~    http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/pages/195-vs-195w

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

        without notice. Check WebSOC for latest updates.

        If an Undergraduate or Graduate course has a "B" or "X"
        restriction, please contact the course instructor directly for
        the authorization codes.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

                                   Spanish

        PREREQUISITES and PLACEMENT

        For all placement-related questions, especially regarding
        enrollment in lower division Spanish language courses, please
        consult the Spanish Placement Table at
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanishandportuguese/language/placement.php

        For information on the Spanish major, please visit the following
        link:
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanishandportuguese/major-spanish

        For information on the Spanish minor, please visit the following
        link:
        http://catalogue.uci.edu/schoolofhumanities/departmentofspanishandportuguese/spanish_minor

        For information on the minor for Spanish-English Bilingual
        Education, please visit the following link:
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/spanish-english-bilingual-education-minor

        Contact the Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu, at
        (949) 824-6207, or visit their Web site at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a test.

        STUDENTS ARE REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST TWO CLASS MEETINGS.
        Enrolled students who do not attend the first two class meetings
        may be dropped from the instructor's roll. These students will
        be required to formally drop the course.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Sciences                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social         ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in     ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Sciences is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in    ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Sciences is the    ###
   ###  end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Change of grade options or variable     ###
   ###  units beginning weeks 3-10 must be made through Student Access.  ###
   ###  Courses for the School's math requirement and major requirements ###
   ###  must be completed with letter grade only.                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQ: If you received AP credit or transferred courses that    ###
   ###  are considered a pre-req, please go to                           ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php to be        ###
   ###  cleared to enroll in the desired course.                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  EXCESS UNITS: All students are restricted to 18-unit initially,  ###
   ###  and will automatically lift to 20 units. If you would like to    ###
   ###  request more than 20 units and have a UC GPA of at least 3.0,    ###
   ###  please fill out the form found here:                             ###
   ###  http://www.undergrad.socsci.uci.edu/ssusa/forms.php The School   ###
   ###  of Social Sciences will wait to process requests until the       ###
   ###  18-unit cap is lifted. No exceptions.                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  RESTRICTIONS: Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some    ###
   ###  School of Social Sciences courses will be restricted to School   ###
   ###  or majors only until Monday, MARCH 20th by noon.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  AUTHORIZATION CODES: For courses with "B" or "X" restriction,    ###
   ###  please contact the instructor of the course.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  REPEAT STUDENTS: If you wish to repeat an undergraduate course,  ###
   ###  please note the repeat restriction will be lifted on Monday,     ###
   ###  MARCH 20th by noon.                                              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

		      Schedule of Classes    Thursday, March 9, 2023

Search Criteria:
    Department: STATS
    Exclude cancelled courses


Spring Quarter, 2023      Registration for term ends on Wednesday, March 15, 2023


   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                 Statistics

         RESTRICTIONS: Most STATS courses will be initially restricted
        to majors in Donald Bren School of Information and Computer
        Sciences ONLY. Some courses will be additionally restricted to
        specific majors and/or level(s) of standing. For restriction
        details and timeline:
        http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php

        WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in
        communication with that course's instructor to arrange for
        access to course matierals and submission of any assignments
        while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing
        coursework DOES NOT guarantee a seat in the course.

        DISCUSSION &amp; LABS: Discussion and lab sections begin meeting
        AFTER the first lecture unless otherwise specified by the course
        instructor. Always check for messages from your instructors
        before the start of instruction.

        B or X Restricted Courses: Courses with a B or X restriction
        require an authorization code from the instructor to enroll.
       _________________________________________________________________

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###      Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For ICS course updates, visit the ICS Course Updates webpage:    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Undergraduate courses:                                           ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Course_updates.php              ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Graduate courses: http://ics.uci.edu/grad/Course_updates.php     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  It is incumbent on the student to check the restriction status   ###
   ###  and seating availability of a course before adding or attempting ###
   ###  to make changes to their study list.                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  COURSE PREREQUISITES ARE STRICTLY ENFORCED. The School of ICS    ###
   ###  WILL DROP students who do not meet the required course. These    ###
   ###  drops may take place at any time after grades are posted until   ###
   ###  Friday of Week 2. Note that meeting the prerequisites for a      ###
   ###  course does not guarantee a seat in that course.                 ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  WAITLIST: Students waitlisted for any ICS course should be in    ###
   ###  communication with that course's instructor to arrange for       ###
   ###  access to course materials and submission of any assignments     ###
   ###  while on the waitlist. Being on the waitlist or completing       ###
   ###  coursework DOES NOT guarantee a set in the course.               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DEADLINES TO ADD/DROP/CHANGE GRADE OPTION FOR ALL SCHOOL OF ICS  ###
   ###  COURSES                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 1: Courses with an early deadline to    ###
   ###  add/drop/change grade option are noted with a comment in the     ###
   ###  Schedule of Classes. Permission from the instructor and an       ###
   ###  authorization code will be required after Week 1 to add or drop  ###
   ###  these courses.                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  5:00pm on Friday of Week 2: The deadline to add/drop/change      ###
   ###  grade option in WebReg is 5:00pm on Friday, April 14, 2023. The  ###
   ###  Bren Schol of ICS strictly adheres to and enforces this deadline ###
   ###  for both undergraduate and graduate courses.                     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADDING, DROPPING, OR CHANGING GRADE OPTION AFTER WEEK 2:         ###
   ###  Students must submit an Enrollment Exception request online      ###
   ###  through StudentAccess. Exception requests will only be approved  ###
   ###  for extenuating and documented circumstances outside of the      ###
   ###  student's control. For more information on ICS policies:         ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/policies/Add_Drop_ChangeOption.php  ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  GRADUATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN UNDERGRADUATE COURSES: Graduate   ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS undergraduate level course  ###
   ###  must submit a request to ICS Undergraduate Students Affairs.     ###
   ###  Priority for seating in undergraduate courses is given first to  ###
   ###  undergraduate students. Unauthorized students found enrolled in  ###
   ###  undergraduate courses WILL BE DROPPED by ICS Student Affairs.    ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  UNDERGRADUATE ENROLLMENT IN GRADUATE COURSES: Undergraduate      ###
   ###  students seeking to enroll in an ICS graduate level course must  ###
   ###  obtain a written permission from the instructor before           ###
   ###  submitting a request for an authorization to ICS Graduate        ###
   ###  Student Affairs. Priority for seating in graduate courses is     ###
   ###  given first to graduate students. Graduate level courses taken   ###
   ###  as an undergraduate will not count toward a graduate degree      ###
   ###  program.                                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DCE CONCURRENT ENROLLMENT: Only courses that show as "OPEN" in   ###
   ###  the Schedule of Classes may be requested. Approval of requests   ###
   ###  is contingent on seating availability and prerequisite           ###
   ###  eligibility. For more information:                               ###
   ###  http://www.ics.uci.edu/ugrad/sao/Concurrent_Enrollment.php       ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

  ~     freshmen until the day the 18-unit enrollment

  ~     will be open to all lower-division
  ~     undergraduates. For more information on Freshman
  ~     Seminars, see the website at
  ~     http://www.freshmanseminar.uci.edu or call the
  ~     Undergraduate/Undeclared Advising Program at
  ~     949-824-6987.

   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                     School of Social Ecology                      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Social       ###
   ###  Ecology is Friday of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in      ###
   ###  WebReg.                                                          ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units    ###
   ###  via WebReg for majors in the School of Social Ecology is Friday  ###
   ###  of Week 2 by 5:00PM.                                             ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Social Ecology ###
   ###  is Friday of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  SCHOOL &amp; MAJOR COURSES: All courses taken to fulfill a school or ###
   ###  major requirement must be taken for a letter grade unless the    ###
   ###  course is offered on a P/NP basis.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  IMPORTANT DEADLINES: Students are responsible for meeting all    ###
   ###  deadlines. For a list of important deadlines go to:              ###
   ###  http://students.soceco.uci.edu/pages/deadlines-and-dates COURSE  ###
   ###  OFFERINGS/TIMES/DAYS ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE.       ###
   ###  CONSULT the Searchable SOC at https://www.reg.uci.edu/ FOR THE    ###
   ###  MOST CURRENT INFORMATION                                         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  FIELD STUDY: Students are encouraged to begin planning for Field ###
   ###  Study 1-2 quarters in advance. For more information and          ###
   ###  important deadlines for Field Study, see the following website:  ###
   ###  http://fieldstudy.soceco.uci.edu/                                ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  For courses with a "B" or "X" restriction, please contact the    ###
   ###  instructor of the course.                                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Due to the volume of majors, enrollment in some School of Social ###
   ###  Ecology courses will be restricted to School or majors only      ###
   ###  until Tuesday, March 14th at noon.                               ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Please note: The majority of classes in the School of Social     ###
   ###  Ecology will be restricted to specific schools or majors until   ###
   ###  Tuesday, March 14th by noon. whether or not an L or N            ###
   ###  restriction is listed in the Restrictions column on the Schedule ###
   ###  of Classes. Please visit the General Catalogue to see which      ###
   ###  majors are eligible to add our lower division courses at this    ###
   ###  time.                                                            ###
   ###                                                                   ###

   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###

                                 Vietnamese

        For all placement-related questions, please consult the Program
        in Global Languages and Communication Placement table at
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/glc/language/programs.php.

        Contact the UCI Academic Testing Center at testcenter@uci.edu,
        (949) 824-6207, or visit their website at
        http://www.testingcenter.uci.edu/ for placement test dates and
        details on registering for a test.

        If you have any questions, please contact the Program in Global
        Languages and Communication at hum-glc@uci.edu.

        Students are REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE FIRST CLASS MEETING.
        Enrolled students who do not attend the first day WILL BE
        DROPPED from the instructor's roll and their spots will be given
        away. These students will be required to formally drop the
        course.

   #########################################################################
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###                       School of Humanities                        ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  DROP: The deadline to drop courses in the School of Humanities   ###
   ###  is the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Drops can be made in WebReg.     ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  CHANGE: The deadline to change grade option or variable units is ###
   ###  the end of Week 2 by 5:00PM. Changes can be made in WebReg.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  ADD: The deadline to add courses in the School of Humanities is  ###
   ###  the end of week 2 by 5:00PM. Adds can be made in WebReg.         ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  Any exception to the add or drop deadline must be requested as   ###
   ###  an Enrollment Exception via the online StudentAccess system      ###
   ###  after second week for DROPs and ADDs and requires approval of    ###
   ###  the Undergraduate Dean. For more information, please visit       ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/add_drop.php.   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  PREREQUISITES:                                                   ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   ###  If you satisfied prerequisites for a course at another college,  ###
   ###  you must contact your academic counseling office to activate     ###
   ###  your eligibility to enroll in the course. School of Humanities   ###
   ###  majors can submit requests via the on-line Course Authorization  ###
   ###  Form available at                                                ###
   ###  http://www.humanities.uci.edu/undergrad/students/forms.php.      ###
   ###                                                                   ###
   #########################################################################

       _________________________________________________________________

                                   Writing

        PLEASE BE ADVISED

        Writing courses will have a "B" or "X" restriction starting on
        the first day of instruction. Students will need to contact the
        instructor to obtain an authorization code to add, drop, or
        change the grading option for the class.

        Waitlists for Writing courses will not be activated.

        ADD/DROP Policy during the FIRST and SECOND week of Instruction
        for Composition Courses.

        Students who are permitted to add or drop a Writing Course after
        the first day of instruction must obtain an authorization code
        from the instructor of the section. Students WILL NOT be
        authorized to add a Writing Course after week 1.

        After the second week of the term students will no longer be
        permitted to drop except through petition.

        Students enrolled in Entry-Level and Lower-Division Writing
        courses are REQUIRED TO ATTEND THE ENTIRE FIRST CLASS MEETING.
        Enrolled students who do not show up on the first day WILL BE
        DROPPED from the instructor's roll and their spot will be given
        away. These students will still be required to formally drop the
        course.

        For more information about Composition courses and
        prerequisites, visit the Program website:
        http://www.humanities.uci.edu/comp/
       _________________________________________________________________
